---
// v0.9.4 dashboard route — release v0.9.4 of chepherd.
//
// Closes #567 per the URL-versioning rule operator codified
// 2026-05-28 (documented in v0.9.3.astro and re-affirmed in #297):
// each release ships its own /vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH/ route. The
// v0.9.4 milestone closed earlier today (71 wave PRs) WITHOUT
// shipping this route — #567 caught the gap.
//
// What's new vs /v0.9.3/ (high-level — see v0.9.4 milestone for
// the full 71-PR + 38-issue scope):
//
//   - Runner-process-split EPIC #453 CLOSED: chepherd-runner is
//     its own process, owns the PTY, hosts per-session A2A
//     endpoints. chepherd-daemon retired its in-process A2A
//     surface (#466 Wave R5 + 410-Gone deprecation chain).
//   - mTLS daemon-to-daemon federation (#487 Wave T3 + #527 T3.1)
//     with cross-pinned CAs.
//   - Per-runner JWT validation against home daemon JWKS
//     (#486 Wave T1).
//   - Push notifications (#482 Wave A3): webhook delivery on
//     Task state transitions, body-blind hub relay.
//   - Headless mode + iogrid integration (#499-#503 Wave H):
//     chepherd-runner --headless per-task ephemeral lifecycle +
//     HTTP API + per-task credential injection + recipe-based
//     execution + AUTH_REQUIRED chain.
//   - chepherd.org hub binary (#491 Wave F1 + F5/F6/F7/F8 follow-ups):
//     SDP signaling + TURN relay + reverse-proxy fallback +
//     cross-org JWT federation.
//   - WebRTC DataChannel transport (#492 Wave F2): 1.58× latency
//     improvement over HTTP fallback.
//   - Knock pattern (#472-#476 Wave K): runner writes
//     [chepherd-knock taskID=<uuid> from=<name>] marker;
//     receiver agent calls chepherd.get_task via MCP to fetch
//     the A2A task envelope.
//   - Audit aggregation (#489 Wave AU2 + #490 AU3):
//     per-runner audit events persisted in daemon + dashboard
//     /audit page with filtering and per-agent view.
//
// Mounts the same AuthGate shell as v0.9.3 (the v0.9 wizard +
// dashboard component tree under web/src/components/v09/ is the
// canonical UI; only the version badge in the header changes
// per-release).
//
// Per the operator's URL-versioning rule, /v0.9.3/ should 301
// redirect to /v0.9.4/ for one release window. That redirect
// lives in middleware/server config — out of scope for this
// route file.
// #728 — calm is now the default dashboard (operator-picked UX revamp,
// replacing the rejected #709 fixed-shell). Mounts the calm root (its own
// login gate + fetch-auth wrapper), mirroring /ux-calm/. The legacy v09
// AuthGate tree stays reachable at /v0.9.3/; the other exploration variants
// remain at /ux-mission|studio|mux|board/ until the operator purges them.
import Dashboardcalm from '../components/calm/Dashboardcalm.svelte';
import '../styles/global.css';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>chepherd v0.9.4 — workspace</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <style>
      html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; height: 100vh; overflow: hidden; }
      body { font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Dashboardcalm client:load version="v0.9.4" />
  </body>
</html>
